cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as document clustering and focuses on distinguishing unnatural language from natural language. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information extraction, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The statistical model used in the paper suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Learning). The paper's focus on NLP tasks and the use of a multiclass classification model suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's use of a corpus and experiments involving machine learning suggest that it could also be categorized under cs.DL (Machine Learning).
